This is an OWLISH DTS release.

1) OWLISH rips their files to a .gi ISO file format and you need RecordNow Max to burn it to CD. I know of no way to mount or unpack this format, you just have to burn it.

2) It's in DTS 5.1 sound, which means you need a 5.1 sound system to play this file properly.

If you have a outboard CD or DVD player connected to a reciever that has a DTS decoding chip, that is ideal

If you rip the CDDA file to a .wav file, VLC media player will play it in 2 channels.

Otherwise, you can play the wav file with WinAmp (with an ASIO out  plugin) or with PowerDVD platinum.
